section.text:
Done, Done, 11/28/2020, , use condoms with every sexual encounter , Std screening - New ·Instructions: You have been diagnosed today with a bacterial vaginal infection Please complete entire course of antibiotics, please refrain from drinking alcohol when taking oral medication. Remember to avoid harsh soaps, douches, vaginal washes, and sprays, as this could be contributing to your symptoms. If your symptoms don't resolve in after completion of medication please return to clinic for further screening., UTI - Comment Only ·Instructions: make sure to finish out antibiotics
You have been diagnosed with a urinary tract infection, please make sure to complete your full course of antibiotics. A sample of your urine has been sent to the lab for a urine culture which will determine what type of bacteria is causing your symptoms. If your symptoms don't resolve in 3 to 5 days, please follow up for further screening. Make sure to drink plenty of water, make sure to urinate after intercourse, and avoid holding your urine., brief (1-3 elements), Avery Ramsey is a 32 Years Old Male ( DOB 07/04/1987) report burning with urination and penile discharge for several days was diagnosed with an UTI 1 month ago and did not finish the antibiotics also wants STD testing reports having unprotected sex with 1 partner , No, No, No, No, No, brief (1-3 elements), I called this patient today to initiate a telehealth appointment but there was no answer. The call went straight to voicemail. I left a voice message with my contact information at Komed Internal Medicine. I instructed the patient to call back as soon as possible. , DYSURIA - New will repeat sti, plus u/a/cx. advised increase fluids. no sex until results known. consider PrEP., pt's last STI testing was 1/24/20, all negative. c/o "irritation" in penile area, generally and with urination. no discharge. Sexually active w 2 partners since last test, both unprotected., No, No, No
